Tin Can Linux is a tiny linux distribution "made from scraps I found on the
internetâ„¢.

=== Building
============

Run './bootstrap' to create an initial rootfs. Then, all the packages must be
rebuilt from inside the chroot. See the website for detailed instructions on
building Tin Can Linux yourself. (coming soon)

=== Inspiration
===============

Projects I took inspiration from / resources I used, in no particular order:

- Mussel (https://github.com/firasuke/mussel)
- StaLi (https://sta.li)
- Linux from Scratch (https://linuxfromscratch.org)
- Kiss Linux (https://kisslinux.github.io)

